webpackJsonp([89365875290243],{5027:function(t,e){t.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h2>3 by 3 Determinants</h2>\n<p>Consider the following matrix, which we will call A:</p>\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <td style="background-color: white">a</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">b</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">c</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style="background-color: white">d</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">e</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">f</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style="background-color: white">g</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">h</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">i</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n<p>Then the determinant of this matrix, denoted <em>det(A)</em>, is given by:</p>\n<p><em>det(A) = a * (e * i - h * f) - b * (d * i - f * g) + c * (d * h - e * g)</em></p>\n<p>Please keep in mind the order of operations in the expression above.</p>\n<p>For example, consider the following matrix, which we will call B:</p>\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <td style="background-color: white">1</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">2</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">3</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style="background-color: white">0</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">-3</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">5</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td style="background-color: white">-10</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">4</td>\n    <td style="background-color: white">7</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n<p><em>det(B)</em> is given by the formula above. We apply the formula below:</p>\n<p><em>det(B) = 1 * ( (-3) * 7 - 5 * 4) - 2 * ( 0 * 7 - 5 * (-10)) + 3 * (0 * 4 - (-3) * (-10))</em>, which we simplify to:</p>\n<p><em>det(B) = 1 * ((-21) - 20) - 2 * (0 - (-50)) + 3 * (0 - (30))</em>, which we simplify to:</p>\n<p><em>det(B) = (-41) - 100 - 90 = -231</em></p>\n<h4>More information:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://www.mathsisfun.com/algebra/matrix-determinant.html">MathIsFun</a> - an explanation of the math behind calculating the determinants of 2x2, 3x3, and even nxn matrices.</li>\n<li><a href="http://www.wolframalpha.com/widgets/view.jsp?id=7fcb0a2c0f0f41d9f4454ac2d8ed7ad6">Wolfram Alpha</a> - an online widget for calculating the determinants of 3x3 matrices.</li>\n<li><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Determinant">Wikipedia</a> - an explanation between the meaning of the determinant.</li>\n</ul>',fields:{slug:"/mathematics/3-by-3-determinants/"},frontmatter:{title:"3 by 3 Determinants"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/mathematics/3-by-3-determinants/"}}}});
